<section>
    <h2>Guide</h2>
    <p>Once downloaded, simply run the executable as an administrator (as the host application needs to be able to listen for incoming web requests)</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>How does it work</h2>
    <p>host application running in background on gaming machine</p>
    <p>acts as a web host</p>
    <p>devices on same network can access the host app</p>
    <p>not accessible out side of network unless you open ports</p>
    <p>UIs are simply html so can be customised</p>
    <p>each control on the ui can be bound to different actions and buttons</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>User interfaces</h2>
    <p>The user interfaces used by Dillon are key to how it works. Using lovingly crafted front-ends the tool can be used to enrich gaming experiences.</p>
